"```sql\nSELECT \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM gasstations \n     WHERE Country = 'CZE' AND Segment = 'Discount') - \n    (SELECT COUNT(*) \n     FROM gasstations \n     WHERE Country = 'SVK' AND Segment = 'Discount') AS Difference;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the difference in the number of \"Discount\" gas stations between the Czech Republic and Slovakia by counting the relevant entries in the `gasstations` table for each country and subtracting the two counts."